Chief Thandisizwe Diko the second, has died. The chief of the AmaBhaca Nation passed away in an Eastern Cape hospital. He was the husband of suspended presidential spokesperson, Khusela Diko. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 Editor's note: This story has been updated JOHANNESBURG - Chief Thandisizwe Diko II has died. He was the leader of the KwaBhaca Great Kingdom and the husband of suspended Presidential Spokesperson Khusela Diko. READ: Diko, Masuku disciplinary hearings continue Chief Thandisizwe Diko II passed away on Sunday afternoon after a short illness. He was 43 years old. He has been linked to controversy in recent months. His wife, Khusela Diko, was suspended from her position earlier this month after a company belonging to the Chief - Royal Bhaca Projects - was awarded a R125-million PPE tender by the Gauteng Health Department. It later emerged that the couple were close friends with then Gauteng Health MEC Bandile Masuku. Chief Thandisizwe Diko II has died. He was the husband of Khusela Diko. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/dIC7ZsWWUf